476%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fjoe-scarborough-surprised-very-disappointed-msnbc-1236073476%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Slamming%20China%20with%20tariffs%20is%20a%20mistake%2C%20and%20the%20US%20can%20do%20one%20big%20thing%20to%20support%20key%20industries%2C%20Yale%20economist%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Biden%2C%20Xi%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66956d819caa6ed01e01b996%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20(R)%20and%20China's%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20(L)%20meet%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%20Nusa%20Dua%20on%20the%20Indonesian%20resort%20island%20of%20Bali%20on%20November%2014%2C%202022.%3Cp%3ESAUL%20LOEB%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20is%20taking%20an%20unnecessarily%20tough%20stance%20on%20China%2C%20Stephen%20Roach%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Yale%20professor%20told%20the%20Odd%20Lots%20podcast%20that%20reducing%20the%20deficit%20is%20a%20better%20way%20to%20improve%20the%20US%20economy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERoach%20criticized%20the%20%26quot%3Bvilified%26quot%3B%20rhetoric%20around%20China.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20needs%20to%20readjust%20its%20approach%20to%20China%20or%20risk%20deep%20and%20unnecessary%20fallout%20between%20the%20world's%20two%20biggest%20economies%2C%20Yale%20economist%20Stephen%20Roach%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Morgan%20Stanley%20China%20chairman%20blasted%20each%20country's%20mounting%20antagonism%20on%20Bloomberg's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-07-15%2Fstephen-roach-warns-of-potentially-disastrous-us-policy-towards-china%3Fsrnd%3Dmarkets-vp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOdd%20Lots%20podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sharing%20dim%20views%20on%20rising%20trade%20barriers.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20was%20the%20first%20to%20initiate%20higher%20tariffs%20against%20Beijing%20in%20his%20first%20term%2C%20restrictions%20have%20continued%20to%20expand%20under%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20similar%20setup%20to%20the%201980's%20face-off%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Japan%2C%20Roach%20said.%20As%20a%20manufacturing%20slump%20roiled%20US%20industry%20in%20that%20decade%2C%20Washington%20incorrectly%20put%20the%20blame%20on%20its%20trade%20deficit%20with%20Japan%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20end%20game%20was%20quite%20tough%20for%20Japan.%20Japan%20went%20from%20a%20growth%20miracle%20to%20a%20growth%20bust%2C%20went%20through%20arguably%20three%20lost%20decades%20of%20near%20economic%20stagnation%2C%20a%20considerable%20amount%20of%20which%20was%20an%20outgrowth%20of%20the%20currency%20policy%20that%20we%20and%20other%20developed%20nations%20imposed%20on%20Japan%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20seems%20to%20be%20happening%20with%20modern-day%20China.%20Throughout%20the%20current%20election%20cycle%2C%20Trump%20has%20pushed%20for%20much%20higher%20tariffs%20on%20imports%20from%20the%20country%2C%20arguing%20that%20this%20will%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariff-plan-inflation-policy-impact-trade-war-china-rates-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboost%20US%20production%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20protect%20industries.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Biden%20has%20applied%20new%20restrictions%20on%20advanced%20technologies%20coming%20from%20China%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-house-joe-biden-hikes-tariffs-on-chinese-made-evs-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectric%20vehicles%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20batteries.%20He's%20said%20the%20reasoning%20is%20to%20allow%20US%20domestic%20industries%20to%20mature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there's%20a%20better%20approach%20to%20growing%20domestically%20than%20slapping%20tariffs%20on%20competitors%2C%20Roach%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Trump%20and%20Biden%20should%20focus%20on%20reducing%20the%20country's%20budget%20deficit.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20way%2C%20the%20economy%20has%20the%20proceeds%20to%20invest%20domestically%2C%20whether%20for%20research%20and%20development%2C%20domestic%20infrastructure%2C%20or%20human%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20there's%20a%20lot%20that%20we%20can%20do%2C%20but%20politically%20it's%20not%20attractive%20and%20not%20palatable%20to%20short-term%20focused%20American%20politicians%2C%26quot%3B%20Roach%20said.%20Trump%20and%20Biden%20have%20each%20worsened%20the%20federal%20debt%20trajectory%20more%20than%20all%20previous%20presidents%20combined%2C%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20was%20the%20case%20with%20Japan%2C%20blaming%20trade%20deficits%20for%20internal%20issues%20is%20a%20misunderstanding%20of%20international%20economics%2C%20Roach%20said%20%E2%80%94%20no%20one%20country%20is%20at%20fault.%20And%20even%20when%20trade%20is%20reduced%2C%20its%20manufacturing%20capacity%20simply%20is%20picked%20up%20by%20other%20economies%20that%20trade%20with%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoach%20also%20dismissed%20talking%20points%20that%20trade%20restrictions%20serve%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fchina-economy-us-growth-xi-jinping-biden-national-security-chips-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enational%20security%3C%2Fa%3E%20barrier%20against%20supposed%20Chinese%20malintent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20politicians%20are%20eager%20and%20aggressive%20to%20warn%20of%20consequences%20based%20on%20the%20presumption%20of%20intent%20that%20they%20have%20not%20been%20able%20and%20are%20unwilling%20to%20validate%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20know%20that's%20an%20unpopular%20view%20to%20hold%20in%20this%20bipartisan%20er