%20me%20the%20wrong%20name%2C%20too%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20do%20some%20damage%20control.%20I%20got%20through%20to%20most%20of%20them%2C%20but%20my%20manager%20never%20got%20it%20right%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20just%20start%20responding%20to%20%26quot%3BAmina.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20complained%20to%20my%20parents%20about%20this%2C%20my%20dad%20scolded%20me%20for%20conceding%20and%20reminded%20me%20that%20he'd%20never%20let%20anyone%20say%20his%20name%20incorrectly.%20But%20in%20this%20case%2C%20correcting%20her%20was%20pointless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnyone%20with%20a%20unique%20name%20knows%20to%20be%20prepared%20for%20clarifying%20questions%20when%20making%20introductions.%20When%20I%20meet%20people%2C%20I%20introduce%20myself%20as%20%26quot%3Bah-mee-tah%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20when%20they%20usually%20respond%20with%20%26quot%3Buh-mee-duh%3F%26quot%3B%20I've%20started%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3Bno%2C%20ah-mee-tah%2C%20with%20a%20'T.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20people%20don't%20hear%20the%20difference%2C%20or%20even%20if%20they%20do%2C%20their%20accents%20just%20take%20over.%20But%20I'm%20at%20least%20making%20an%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20frustrating%2C%20but%20I'm%20grateful%20for%20my%20name.%20It's%20helped%20me%20learn%20to%20advocate%20for%20myself%20and%20be%20aware%20of%20whether%20I'm%20saying%20other's%20names%20correctly.%20I%20deeply%20love%20the%20sound%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-common-name-people-cant-spell-it-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euniqueness%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20meaning%20of%20my%20name%2C%20and%20I%20know%20my%20parents%20put%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20and%20energy%20into%20choosing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20taught%20me%20that%20the%20people%20in%20my%20life%20who%20take%20the%20time%20to%20pronounce%20it%20right%20%E2%80%94%20and%20correct%20others%20%E2%80%94%20are%20the%20ones%20who%20matter%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%